module-whatis "Description: Padb is a Job Inspection Tool for examining and debugging parallel programs, primarily it simplifies the process of gathering stack traces on compute clusters however it also supports a wide range of other functions. Padb supports a number of parallel environments and it works out-of-the-box on the majority of clusters. It's an open source, non-interactive, command line, script-able tool intended for use by programmers and system administrators alike."
